noFlea.name: Tripwire installation kit
noFlea.description: An improvised booby trap kit made of tent pegs and wire with a carabiner. Allows the user to install tripwires on flat surfaces or to conceal explosives on an object.

noFlea.name: Desert Tech MDR 7.62x51 assault rifle T.O 2K24
Stich Profi Stich Defense mod.2 plate carrier (MultiCam) Default
Streamer item case
noFlea.description: A case for compact storage of those strange souvenirs scattered throughout Tarkov, perfect for collectors.

noFlea.name: RSP-30 reactive signal cartridge (Blue)
noFlea.description: A reactive signal cartridge for commanding and maintaining squad interaction. Some Scavs use this flare color to send some kinds of signals. The question is, what do these signals mean?

noFlea.name: RSP-30 reactive signal cartridge (Special Yellow)
noFlea.description: A special cartridge used to signal the right people and collect the special cargo for Prapor.

noFlea.name: Radar station spare parts
noFlea.description: Some spare parts for radar stations. Probably not useful unless you're an advanced radar specialist PMC. Which you probably aren't.

noFlea.name: KOSA UAV electronic jamming device
noFlea.description: The device is designed to suppress UAV guidance systems. Helps to reliably protect any facility from airborne attacks.

noFlea.name: GARY ZONT portable electronic warfare device
noFlea.description: The device suppresses satellite navigation system signals within a several kilometers radius. Sometimes these “umbrellas” can be more important than good body armor.

noFlea.name: MPS Auto Assault-12 Gen 1 12ga automatic shotgun
noFlea.description: The AA-12 (Auto Assault-12) is a reliable full-auto 12-gauge shotgun. The first generation features the high-mounted built-in iron sights. This shotgun is distinguished by its recoil pulse accumulation, which makes the recoil feel smooth without sacrificing fire rate and stopping power. The AA-12 is designed for military and police units. Manufactured by Military Police Systems.

noFlea.name: TG-Vi-24 lethal vaccine
noFlea.description: This vaccine was developed by Therapist and Sanitar. The lethality of an infected patient is extremely high.

noFlea.name: TG-Vi-24 true vaccine
noFlea.description: A modified version of the vaccine with minimal lethality risk. Looks like Therapist and Sanitar have no intention of sharing it.

noFlea.name: Flash drive with special software
noFlea.description: This thumb drive can be used to set up a remote connection to the TerraGroup local servers for Mechanic.

noFlea.name: MPS Auto Assault-12 Gen 2 12ga automatic shotgun
noFlea.description: The AA-12 (Auto Assault-12) is a reliable full-auto 12-gauge shotgun. The second generation features a mount for installing optics. This shotgun is distinguished by its recoil pulse accumulation, which makes the recoil feel smooth without sacrificing fire rate and stopping power. The AA-12 is designed for military and police units. Manufactured by Military Police Systems.

Sako TRG M10 .338 LM bolt-action sniper rifle
noFlea.description: The TRG M10 is a precision bolt-action sniper rifle chambered for the .338 Lapua Magnum cartridge. The TRG M10 is an extremely versatile platform: it easily converts from a proper long-range rifle to a more compact weapon. The rifle is designed to be used by army, police and various special forces of several countries. Manufactured by Sako, which is part of Beretta Defense Technologies holding company.

noFlea.name: Opened case
noFlea.description: This case contains several sealed boxes.

noFlea.name: Contraband box
noFlea.description: A box containing contraband cargo from Peacekeeper. Opening it might not be a good idea.

noFlea.name: Sealed box
noFlea.description: The box is sealed to protect its contents. A multitool is required to open it.

noFlea.name: Opened box
noFlea.description: This box can't hold much, but now you can see what's inside.

noFlea.name: Locked case
noFlea.description: The contents are unknown, but you'll need a key to open it.

noFlea.name: 5.11 Tactical RUSH 100 backpack (Black)
noFlea.description: A tactical backpack with a complex modular system. The arrangement of internal compartments and side straps makes the RUSH 100 a highly versatile backpack that can be adapted to any combat situation.

noFlea.name: Saiga-12K 12ga automatic shotgun
noFlea.description: A modification of the Saiga-12K smoothbore shotgun, enabling fully automatic fire. Hell of a beast.

noFlea.name: PNV-57E night vision goggles
noFlea.description: Despite the fact that this model was manufactured in the 80s, the Soviet quality is still evident. The picture might not be as good as gen 2 or gen 3 night vision, but it's definitely worth its price.

noFlea.name: What You Seek poster
noFlea.description: A rare What You Seek poster. Only the most hardcore USEC operators can get it.

noFlea.name: I Bear Loot poster
noFlea.description: A rare I Bear Loot poster. Very few BEAR operators can get one of these.

noFlea.name: Minefield map (Reserve)
noFlea.description: Someone had sketched a hand-drawn diagram of the perimeter of the Federal Reserve military base in its northwestern part. According to the notes, there is a gap in the minefield that could be used for a safe exfil.

noFlea.name: Minefield map (Lighthouse)
noFlea.description: Someone was preparing to assault the water treatment plant and had marked out the optimal routes to bypass the minefields. One of the routes goes toward the bay. Looks like there's a safe exfil route from the coast.

noFlea.name: Minefield map (Woods)
noFlea.description: Someone has hand-drawn a diagram of the minefield next to the railroad in the nature reserve area. Apparently, you can safely exfil from Priozersk near the railroad bridge.

noFlea.name: Note with code word Voron
noFlea.description: It seems that "Voron" is some kind of cipher or code. If someone has manipulated the exfils from Customs, they must have left access only for their own. The question is, where are these exits?

noFlea.name: Note with code word Onyx
noFlea.description: “Onyx”. If it's not a random scribble, then it's some kind of code. Perhaps one of the Scavs has found a new exfil route out of the city, but only allows access to their own. In a densely built environment, a reliable escape route must be underground.

noFlea.name: Note with code word Adaptation
noFlea.description: There's only one word on the note: “Adaptation”. Looks like a code word. If someone found a new exfil route out of the TerraGroup HQ area, they must have placed their men nearby to keep anyone from the outside from getting to the new exit. In that case, the code would help distinguish friend from foe.

noFlea.name: Note with code word Ark
noFlea.description: The word “Ark” hardly needs to be taken literally. It's more like a code word. There are quite a few locked doors under the Polikhim Factory, leading deeper into the catacombs. Perhaps someone will open the door for you if you know the code word.

noFlea.name: Note with code word Heartbeat
noFlea.description: Someone wrote the word “Heartbeat” on a torn piece of paper. Sounds like one of Sanitar's weird pranks. Or perhaps a code word? If his men have their own exfil routes off Shoreline, they must be using a system of key phrases or signals. Maybe this note will make you look like one of their own.

noFlea.name: Dogtag BEAR
noFlea.description: A special army dogtag with rubber sides serving the purpose of quickly identifying the wounded and deceased in combat. An indicator of the PMC operative's status.

noFlea.name: Dogtag BEAR
noFlea.description: A special stainless steel army dogtag serving the purpose of quickly identifying the wounded and deceased in combat. Available only to the most experienced PMC operatives.

noFlea.name: RSP-30 reactive signal cartridge (Firework)
noFlea.description: RSP-30 is a reactive signal cartridge for commanding and maintaining squad interaction. Multi-star rocket cartridges are used as flares.

noFlea.name: Secure container Kappa (Desecrated)
noFlea.description: A secret TerraGroup invention that has fallen into the hands of the cultists.

noFlea.description: A 7.62x51mm NATO M80A1 cartridge with a 124 grain armor-piercing copper jacket bullet with an exposed hardened steel penetrator, in a stainless steel casing. Designed as a replacement for the M80 cartridge to improve the armor penetration and ballistics of the cartridge as part of a program to eliminate the use of lead in small arms ammunition in the U.S. Army.

armor.name: Crye Precision AVS plate carrier (Ranger Green)
armor.description: The Crye Precision AVS plate carrier equipped with Groin Protector and pouches in assault configuration. One of the most comfortable to wear plate carriers.

armor.name: 6B43 Zabralo-Sh body armor (EMR)
armor.description: The 6B43 bulletproof vest is designed for protection from light weapon bullets - including BP and PP - fragments of grenades, mines, and melee weapons, as well as reducing the risk of after-penetration effects during combat situations.

armor.name: PACA Soft Armor
armor.description: A light but durable and reliable body armor protecting only the vital areas.

armor.name: BNTI Module-3M body armor
armor.description: A lightweight bulletproof vest of class 2 of GOST-R protection, used by private security companies and collection services.

armor.name: ANA Tactical M2 plate carrier (EMR)
armor.description: The M2 vest is created with the use of the best experience of Russian special forces operators. The versatility of the system makes it possible to use this vest both when carrying out urban tasks and when performing tasks on rough terrain. Equipped with additional pouches for 8 magazines. Manufactured by ANA Tactical.

armor.name: MF-UNTAR body armor
armor.description: A class III body armor used by UN soldiers during the UNTAR mission in Tarkov.

armor.name: BNTI Gzhel-K body armor
armor.description: The Gzhel assault bulletproof vest is designed for assault units of the Ministry of Internal Affairs and other law enforcement agencies.

armor.name: 5.11 Tactical TacTec plate carrier (Ranger Green)
armor.description: A plate carrier with a set of pouches for use with assault rifles. Manufactured by 5.11 Tactical.

armor.name: IOTV Gen4 body armor (Full Protection Kit, MultiCam)
armor.description: The Improved Outer Tactical Vest (IOTV) Gen IV is designed to permit maximum freedom of movement required to assume correct firing positions with the agility to execute and maneuver tasks. Optimal design characteristics ensure the best possible weight distribution of both the ballistic body armor system as well as additional load bearing equipment, thus providing enhanced comfort, wear duration, and mobility. Full protection kit.

armor.name: IOTV Gen4 body armor (Assault Kit, MultiCam)
armor.description: The Improved Outer Tactical Vest (IOTV) Gen IV is designed to permit maximum freedom of movement required to assume correct firing positions with the agility to execute and maneuver tasks. Optimal design characteristics ensure the best possible weight distribution of both the ballistic body armor system as well as additional load bearing equipment, thus providing enhanced comfort, wear duration, and mobility. Increased ergonomics assault kit.

armor.name: IOTV Gen4 body armor (High Mobility Kit, MultiCam)
armor.description: The Improved Outer Tactical Vest (IOTV) Gen IV is designed to permit maximum freedom of movement required to assume correct firing positions with the agility to execute and maneuver tasks. Optimal design characteristics ensure the best possible weight distribution of both the ballistic body armor system as well as additional load bearing equipment, thus providing enhanced comfort, wear duration, and mobility. Increased mobility and comfort kit.

armor.name: BNTI Kirasa-N body armor
armor.description: The "Kirasa N" body armor is designed for the army and police special forces of the Russian Federation. The bulletproof vest provides circular protection of the human torso. Elements of the damper provide ventilation of the under armor space and reduce the blunt damage.

armor.name: 6B5-16 Zh-86 Uley armored rig (Khaki)
armor.description: The 6B5 bulletproof vest was adopted by the armed forces of the USSR in 1986. Option 6B5-16 is designed to protect against fragments and bullets of fire arms (class 3 protection, titanium). Also has several pouches for magazines and other equipment.

armor.name: 6B5-15 Zh-86 Uley armored rig (Flora)
armor.description: The 6B5 bulletproof vest was adopted by the armed forces of the USSR in 1986. Option 6B5-15 is designed for assault units (class 4 protection, boron carbide). Also has several pouches for magazines and other equipment.

armor.name: 6B13 assault armor (Flora)
armor.description: The main armored vest for personnel of combat units of the ground forces, airborne troops, marines, etc. The vest is designed to protect vital organs from being hit by firearms, shell fragments, mines, grenades, and cold weapons, reducing the severity of armor contusion injury when performing combat missions. Flora camouflage version.

armor.name: 6B13 assault armor (EMR)
armor.description: The main armored vest for personnel of combat units of the ground forces, airborne troops, marines, etc. The vest is designed to protect vital organs from being hit by firearms, shell fragments, mines, grenades, and cold weapons, reducing the severity of blunt injury when performing combat missions. EMR (Digital Flora) camouflage version.

armor.name: 6B13 M assault armor (Killa Edition)
armor.description: A tan version of the 6B13 armored vest that was personally modified by Killa with a revolutionary and trendy design.

armor.name: 6B23-2 body armor (Mountain Flora)
armor.description: The Zabralo-8 main armored vest for personnel of combat units of the ground forces, airborne troops, marines, etc. The vest is designed to protect vital organs from being hit by firearms, shell fragments, mines, grenades, and cold weapons, reducing the severity of armor contusion injury when performing combat missions.

armor.name: 6B23-1 body armor (EMR)
armor.description: The "Zabralo-8" armored vest for personnel of combat units of the Russian ground forces, airborne troops, marines, etc. The vest is designed to protect vital organs from being hit by firearms, shell fragments, mines, grenades, and cold weapons, reducing the severity of blunt injury when performing combat missions.

armor.name: BNTI Zhuk body armor (Press)
armor.description: An armored vest for journalists working in combat zones.

armor.name: BNTI Zhuk body armor (EMR)
armor.description: An armored vest designed for assault units. Based on the Gzhel armor, serving as its lightweight copy.

armor.name: HighCom Trooper TFO body armor (MultiCam)
armor.description: A plate armor vest by HighCom, popular among USEC PMCs. MultiCam camouflage version.

armor.name: ANA Tactical M1 plate carrier (Olive Drab)
armor.description: The M1 vest is created with the use of the best experience of Russian special forces operators. The versatility of the system makes it possible to use this vest both when carrying out city tasks and when performing tasks on rough terrain. Equipped with additional pouches. Manufactured by ANA Tactical.

armor.name: WARTECH TV-110 plate carrier (Coyote)
armor.description: The LBS TV-110 plate carrier equipped with a set of pouches. Manufactured by WARTECH.

armor.name: FORT Redut-M body armor
armor.description: “Redut-M” is a modified version of the well-proven Redut body armor, which is in service of special units of the FSB. The vest is based on advanced technologies in the field of individual armor. Due to the optimized form of armor elements and the outer cover with a special damping-ventilation system, the Redut M armored vest has excellent functional qualities, which facilitates active actions, including those associated with the use of vehicles and in confined spaces.

armor.name: FORT Redut-T5 body armor (Smog)
armor.description: The FORT "Redut T5" armor vest is a reinforced version of Redut armor series, designed with account of the many years of experience in counter-terrorism operations in the Russian Federation. Smog camouflage version.

armor.name: 6B3TM-01 armored rig (Khaki)
armor.description: The 6B3 modified general army body armor under the index 6B3TM-01. Actively used during the war in Afghanistan. It has a comprehensive titanium class 4 (Russian GOST) protection and a set of several pouches for magazines and grenades.

armor.name: Ars Arma A18 Skanda plate carrier (MultiCam)
armor.description: A plate carrier equipped with a set of pouches in assault configuration. Manufactured by Ars Arma.

armor.name: 6B2 body armor (Flora)
armor.description: An old army body armor from Afghanistan war times, mainly designed to protect against pistol bullets and explosion fragments. It fulfilled its mission, but was soon replaced by bulletproof vests with differentiated protection.

armor.name: LBT-6094A Slick Plate Carrier (Black)
armor.description: A simple yet effective plate carrier by London Bridge Trading company. The most minimalistic design intended for use with chest rigs. Black version.

armor.name: Ars Arma CPC MOD.1 plate carrier (A-TACS FG)
armor.description: The first generation of the modified CPC plate carrier originally designed by Crye Precision and adapted by Ars Arma for use by special forces of the Russian Federation. This modular body armor is based on a polymer harness that fits the thorax, which avoids the plate carrier backlash during active movement and also contributes to a more even distribution of weight. Made in the assault configuration of pouches. Manufactured by Ars Arma.

armor.name: FORT Defender-2 body armor
armor.description: The FORT OK "Defender-2" operational kit is a modification of the popular body armor FORT "Defender" designed for both VIP and for employees of operational combat units. The kit uses the maximum capabilities of the modular principle of building armor based on steel plates.

armor.name: NPP KlASS Korund-VM body armor (Black)
armor.description: The NPP KlASS Korund-VM heavy bulletproof vest, adopted by the units of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russia.

armor.name: 5.11 Tactical Hexgrid plate carrier
armor.description: The Hexgrid plate carrier with smooth ergonomic access that allows comfortable movement, intended for use with chest rigs. Manufactured by 5.11 Tactical.

armor.name: LBT-6094A Slick Plate Carrier (Coyote Tan)
armor.description: A simple yet effective plate carrier by London Bridge Trading company. The most minimalistic design intended for use with chest rigs. Coyote Tan version.

armor.name: LBT-6094A Slick Plate Carrier (Olive Drab)
armor.description: A simple yet effective plate carrier by London Bridge Trading company. The most minimalistic design intended for use with chest rigs. Olive Drab version.

armor.name: PACA Soft Armor (Rivals Edition)
armor.description: A light but durable and reliable body armor protecting only the vital areas, fitted with class 2 (Russian GOST) armor plates. Twitch Rivals 2021 special edition.

armor.name: NFM THOR Concealable Reinforced Vest body armor
armor.description: The THOR Concealable Reinforced Vest enables the overt or covert carrying of soft ballistic panels providing 360 degrees protection against high-speed fragments and handgun ammunition. Adding hard ballistic plates enables protection against rifle ammunition for the vital organs. The ergonomic shape of the soft ballistic panels and the position of the back plate combined with the integrated lumbar support belt provides comfort and stability close to the body’s center of mass. Manufactured by NFM.

armor.name: Crye Precision AVS plate carrier (Tagilla Edition)
armor.description: Tagilla's well-worn plate carrier based on the AVS module system by Crye Precision. Equipped with a front panel with three magazine pouches. And that's pretty much it. Nothing more, nothing less.

armor.name: NFM THOR Integrated Carrier body armor
armor.description: The THOR full protection assault body armor equipped with soft and hard armor elements to protect against shrapnel and bullets of pistol and rifle calibers. Manufactured by NFM.

armor.name: CQC Osprey MK4A plate carrier (Protection, MTP)
armor.description: The Osprey plate carrier is actively used by the British army and specialists. The Protection preset is provided with the optimal number of pouches for ammunition, grenades and special equipment.

armor.name: CQC Osprey MK4A plate carrier (Assault, MTP)
armor.description: The Osprey plate carrier is actively used by the British army and specialists. The Assault preset features a large amount of pouches for ammunition and grenades.

armor.name: Eagle Industries MMAC plate carrier (Ranger Green)
armor.description: The Eagle Industries Multi-Mission Tactical Vest (MMAC) is a traditional profile vest offering modularity and scalability. The tactical vest is constructed of MIL-SPEC 500 denier nylon and is fully MOLLE/PALS compatible. It features padded shoulders with detachable retention loops, push-to-talk (PTT) attachment points at upper left and right chest and many other features.

armor.name: FirstSpear Strandhogg plate carrier (Ranger Green)
armor.description: Taking its name from an Old Norse Viking term for a lightning raid, Strandhögg was one of the first formalized battle tactics to use covert infiltrators in advance of an actual raiding operation. Strandhögg was a tactical game-changer in its time, just like the technological advances FirstSpear is bringing forward in this line of plate carriers.

armor.name: S&S Precision PlateFrame plate carrier (Goons Edition)
armor.description: A plate carrier with a minimalistic, lightweight, semi rigid plastic design, which was configured by Big Pipe - member of the Goons squad. Manufactured by S&S Precision.

armor.name: Crye Precision CPC plate carrier (Goons Edition)
armor.description: The CAGE PLATE CARRIER (CPC) offers unrivaled comfort and load support in a low profile plate carrier configuration. The system supports a range of different pouches. In this case, the configuration is made by the leader of the Goons squad - Knight - for conducting assault operations with increased mobility.

armor.name: Tasmanian Tiger SK plate carrier (MultiCam Black)
armor.description: The ultra-light and skeletal TT Plate Carrier SK vest is made primarily from lightweight, thin and durable TPU-laminated Cordura nylon material with a claimed density of at least 700 denier. The design of the vest provides two lightweight covers for plates, adjustable shoulder straps and a light waist jumper. Equipped with a front panel for 4 magazines.

armor.name: NPP KlASS Bagariy plate carrier (EMR)
armor.description: In the second millennium, the equipment of a soldier received serious changes in view of new threats and tasks. A better level of protection was required, so the Russian army needed a reliable and functional body armor. In the mid-2000s, the MVD, which was later reorganized into the Russian Guard, received Bagariy bulletproof vests. Bagariy was used both by ordinary soldiers of the internal troops, and in special forces. Actively was used by PMC BEAR as the main heavy body armor.

armor.name: ECLiPSE RBAV-AF plate carrier (Ranger Green)
armor.description: The BAE ECLiPSE RBAV (Releasable Body Armor Vest, Air Force) variant is designed specifically for the Guardian Angel Weapon System (USAF PJ) and contains several new features not found in other versions.

armor.name: DRD body armor
armor.description: A light but durable and reliable body armor. Special edition from the one and only Dr. Disrespect. Ruthless!

armor.name: Hexatac HPC Plate Carrier (MultiCam Black)
armor.description: A plate carrier by Hexatac. A minimalistic version designed to be used with chest rigs. MultiCam Black version.

armor.name: Shellback Tactical Banshee plate carrier (A-TACS AU)
armor.description: The Banshee Rifle Plate Carrier was designed to meet and exceed the needs of law enforcement, military, and tactical operators. This ultra lightweight, low profile, high-quality plate carrier has great load carrying capacity.

armor.name: WARTECH TV-115 plate carrier (Olive Drab)
armor.description: Operational armor system TV-115 with high-density polyethylene (class 3) plates, protecting only the chest and the back. Manufactured by WARTECH.

armor.name: Eagle Allied Industries MBSS plate carrier (Coyote Brown)
armor.description: The MBSS vest is part of the Maritime Ballistic Survivor System. The vest can be used with flotation inserts to provide buoyancy as it is not equipped with a quick release system. Manufactured by Eagle Allied Industries.

armor.name: Interceptor OTV body armor (UCP)
armor.description: The Interceptor vest consists of a fabric Outer Tactical Vest (OTV) with dorsal and thoracic pockets and two protective ceramic-composite SAPI or ESAPI inserts. The Outer Tactical Vest (OTV) is a basic vest equipped with aramid fabric pouches that protect against ammunition fragments and 9mm handgun bullets.

armor.name: NPP KlASS Kora-Kulon body armor (Black)
armor.description: The Kora-Kulon bulletproof vest is a means of individual armor protection of long-term wear, allowing to perform all types of professional activities of the personnel of the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Ministry of Defense units. The design of the bulletproof vest allows its use in concealed operation under outer clothing. Designed to protect the wearer from firearms and sharp weapons. Black version.

armor.name: NPP KlASS Kora-Kulon body armor (EMR)
armor.description: The Kora-Kulon bulletproof vest is a means of individual armor protection of long-term wear, allowing to perform all types of professional activities of the personnel of the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Ministry of Defense units. The design of the bulletproof vest allows its use in concealed operation under outer clothing. Designed to protect the wearer from firearms and sharp weapons. EMR (Digital Flora) camouflage version.

armor.name: 6B13 M assault armor (Christmas Edition)
armor.description: To celebrate Christmas and the New Year, Killa redesigned his body armor. The armor is now more noticeable, but Killa has never been one for cautious reconnaissance.

rig.name: Crye Precision AVS plate carrier (Ranger Green)
rig.description: The Crye Precision AVS plate carrier equipped with Groin Protector and pouches in assault configuration. One of the most comfortable to wear plate carriers.

rig.name: BlackRock chest rig (Gray)
rig.description: A custom-made chest rig for wearing on top of body armor in urban operations. Sturdy and versatile, it features both MOLLE and ALICE attachment systems.

rig.name: Scav Vest
rig.description: A fisherman's vest can more or less replace the chest rig, if the need is pressing enough.

rig.name: UMTBS 6Sh112 Scout-Sniper chest rig (EMR)
rig.description: The Universal Modular Transport-Combat System (UMTBS) "Scout-Sniper" is officially part of the equipment of the armed forces of the Russian Federation. The vest is designed with a modular approach and can be transformed to suit various specific combat tasks. This system includes the vest base, various purpose pouches, and backpacks. Due to the fact that the vest is based on the MOLLE system, it can be used with various compatible pouches beyond those included with the kit. The belt system has soft bumper pads, and its inside is made from breathable materials.

rig.name: ANA Tactical Alpha chest rig (Olive Drab)
rig.description: "Alpha" is a high-quality chest rig that fully meets the military standards for reliability and functionality. The combination of integrated pouches and MOLLE straps provides the means of carrying a large number of necessary equipment. The vest is designed as a classic chest rig. In this type of vest, all the gear is located in the front and side parts, while the back part is comprised of adjustment belts and straps. Manufactured by ANA Tactical.

rig.name: WARTECH TV-109 + TV-106 chest rig (A-TACS FG)
rig.description: The WARTECH gear rig consisting of the TV-106 Battle Belt and TV-109 heavy suspension system. The shoulder straps are reinforced with foam and have MOLLE straps, and the TV-109 combined with the TV-106 completes the belt system into a full-featured gear rig.

rig.name: WARTECH MK3 TV-104 chest rig (MultiCam)
rig.description: This chest rig platform is designed for placing equipment in the chest and abdomen areas, with an open back. Includes integrated pouches, designed for 8 magazines. Can be used both separately and on top of the armor vest. Manufactured by WARTECH.

rig.name: ANA Tactical M2 plate carrier (EMR)
rig.description: The M2 vest is created with the use of the best experience of Russian special forces operators. The versatility of the system makes it possible to use this vest both when carrying out urban tasks and when performing tasks on rough terrain. Equipped with additional pouches for 8 magazines. Manufactured by ANA Tactical.

rig.name: BlackHawk! Commando chest harness (Desert Tan)
rig.description: Designed for comfort and quick access, this harness puts a lot of additional magazines at the user's fingertips. Manufactured by BlackHawk. Desert Tan version.

rig.name: 5.11 Tactical TacTec plate carrier (Ranger Green)
rig.description: A plate carrier with a set of pouches for use with assault rifles. Manufactured by 5.11 Tactical.

rig.name: 6B5-16 Zh-86 Uley armored rig (Khaki)
rig.description: The 6B5 bulletproof vest was adopted by the armed forces of the USSR in 1986. Option 6B5-16 is designed to protect against fragments and bullets of fire arms (class 3 protection, titanium). Also has several pouches for magazines and other equipment.

rig.name: 6B5-15 Zh-86 Uley armored rig (Flora)
rig.description: The 6B5 bulletproof vest was adopted by the armed forces of the USSR in 1986. Option 6B5-15 is designed for assault units (class 4 protection, boron carbide). Also has several pouches for magazines and other equipment.

rig.name: Poyas-A + Poyas-B gear rig
rig.description: Poyas-A ("Belt-A") is the legendary rig from the Afghan war era. This rig was adopted in 1989 and was used by the GRU Special Forces until the beginning of the 21st century. It comes equipped with an added Poyas-B belt that has 10 pouches for VOG grenades.

rig.name: ANA Tactical M1 plate carrier (Olive Drab)
rig.description: The M1 vest is created with the use of the best experience of Russian special forces operators. The versatility of the system makes it possible to use this vest both when carrying out city tasks and when performing tasks on rough terrain. Equipped with additional pouches. Manufactured by ANA Tactical.

rig.name: WARTECH TV-110 plate carrier (Coyote)
rig.description: The LBS TV-110 plate carrier equipped with a set of pouches. Manufactured by WARTECH.

rig.name: BlackHawk! Commando chest harness (Black)
rig.description: Designed for comfort and quick access, this harness puts a lot of additional magazines at the user's fingertips. Manufactured by BlackHawk. Black version.

rig.name: Dynaforce Triton M43-A chest harness (Black)
rig.description: The Triton M43-A assault chest rig is designed to store and carry ammunition and equipment for use in moderate and hot climates. Manufactured by Dynaforce.

rig.name: 6B3TM-01 armored rig (Khaki)
rig.description: The 6B3 modified general army body armor under the index 6B3TM-01. Actively used during the war in Afghanistan. It has a comprehensive titanium class 4 (Russian GOST) protection and a set of several pouches for magazines and grenades.

rig.name: Haley Strategic D3CRX Chest Harness (Ranger Green)
rig.description: The Haley Strategic D3CRX Combat chest rig is one of the most respected PMC rig systems. Ease and comfort of use are supported by the presence of the optimal number of pouches.

rig.name: Ars Arma A18 Skanda plate carrier (MultiCam)
rig.description: A plate carrier equipped with a set of pouches in assault configuration. Manufactured by Ars Arma.

rig.name: SOE Micro Rig (MultiCam)
rig.description: An extra lightweight and small chest rig with the necessary minimum of pouches. Manufactured by SOE Gear.

rig.name: Velocity Systems MPPV Multi-Purpose Patrol Vest (Wolf Grey)
rig.description: Multi-Purpose Patrol Vest is designed for those patrolling situations where armor is not needed. A lightweight rig with a lot of pouches. Manufactured by Velocity Systems.

rig.name: Spiritus Systems Bank Robber chest rig (MultiCam Black)
rig.description: An ultra-compact and lightweight chest rig for mobility and comfort. Manufactured by Spiritus Systems.

rig.name: Splav Tarzan M22 chest rig (Smog)
rig.description: A simple and fairly practical tactical rig from 2002. It is still actively used by security and law enforcement agencies and civilian shooters in Russia. Smog camouflage version.

rig.name: Ars Arma CPC MOD.1 plate carrier (A-TACS FG)
rig.description: The first generation of the modified CPC plate carrier originally designed by Crye Precision and adapted by Ars Arma for use by special forces of the Russian Federation. This modular body armor is based on a polymer harness that fits the thorax, which avoids the plate carrier backlash during active movement and also contributes to a more even distribution of weight. Made in the assault configuration of pouches. Manufactured by Ars Arma.

rig.name: LBT-1961A Load Bearing Chest Rig (MAS Grey)
rig.description: A tactical load-bearing system designed to carry magazines, grenades, and special equipment, while using low-profile body armor. Manufactured by London Bridge Trading.

rig.name: Direct Action Thunderbolt compact chest rig (Shadow Grey)
rig.description: The Thunderbolt fixed chest rig, containing all the basic utility pouches you'd need. Manufactured by Direct Action.

rig.name: DIY IDEA chest rig
rig.description: A handcrafted chest rig made from IDEA store bags. It's impossible to say that it's reliable and suitable for a wide range of military and tactical applications, but at least it's a good example of a hobo-style rig.

rig.name: Security vest
rig.description: The simplest, life-worn vest of the security services.

rig.name: Gear Craft GC-BSS-MK1 chest rig (A-TACS FG)
rig.description: The new generation shoulder belt system, made for patrol and assault operations.

rig.name: Umka M33-SET1 hunter vest (Olive Drab)
rig.description: The Umka M33-SET1 vest is designed for hunters, travelers, field professionals and security officers.

rig.name: CSA chest rig (Black)
rig.description: The simplest chest rig, sewn hastily from dubious materials. Designed for airsoft. Military use of this model is possible, but not recommended.

rig.name: Azimut SS Zhuk chest harness (Black)
rig.description: A simple nylon bearing system with non-removable pouches. Allows you to carry a fairly impressive amount of ammunition at the expense of convenience.

rig.name: Azimut SS Zhuk chest harness (SURPAT)
rig.description: A simple nylon bearing system with non-removable pouches. Allows you to carry a fairly impressive amount of ammunition at the expense of convenience. SURPAT camouflage version.

rig.name: Crye Precision AVS plate carrier (Tagilla Edition)
rig.description: Tagilla's well-worn plate carrier based on the AVS module system by Crye Precision. Equipped with a front panel with three magazine pouches. And that's pretty much it. Nothing more, nothing less.

rig.name: CQC Osprey MK4A plate carrier (Protection, MTP)
rig.description: The Osprey plate carrier is actively used by the British army and specialists. The Protection preset is provided with the optimal number of pouches for ammunition, grenades and special equipment.

rig.name: CQC Osprey MK4A plate carrier (Assault, MTP)
rig.description: The Osprey plate carrier is actively used by the British army and specialists. The Assault preset features a large amount of pouches for ammunition and grenades.

rig.name: Stich Profi Chest Rig MK2 (Assault, A-TACS FG)
rig.description: The "Chest-Rig" tactical system can be used as an independent piece of equipment or as an addition to body armor without the MOLLE system. Suitable for combat training instructors, special forces units. Assault preset in A-TACS FG camouflage. Manufactured by Stich Profi.

rig.name: Stich Profi Chest Rig MK2 (Recon, A-TACS FG)
rig.description: The "Chest-Rig" tactical system can be used as an independent piece of equipment or as an addition to body armor without the MOLLE system. Suitable for combat training instructors, special forces units. Recon preset in A-TACS FG camouflage. Manufactured by Stich Profi.

rig.name: Eagle Industries MMAC plate carrier (Ranger Green)
rig.description: The Eagle Industries Multi-Mission Tactical Vest (MMAC) is a traditional profile vest offering modularity and scalability. The tactical vest is constructed of MIL-SPEC 500 denier nylon and is fully MOLLE/PALS compatible. It features padded shoulders with detachable retention loops, push-to-talk (PTT) attachment points at upper left and right chest and many other features.

rig.name: FirstSpear Strandhogg plate carrier (Ranger Green)
rig.description: Taking its name from an Old Norse Viking term for a lightning raid, Strandhögg was one of the first formalized battle tactics to use covert infiltrators in advance of an actual raiding operation. Strandhögg was a tactical game-changer in its time, just like the technological advances FirstSpear is bringing forward in this line of plate carriers.

rig.name: S&S Precision PlateFrame plate carrier (Goons Edition)
rig.description: A plate carrier with a minimalistic, lightweight, semi rigid plastic design, which was configured by Big Pipe - member of the Goons squad. Manufactured by S&S Precision.

rig.name: Crye Precision CPC plate carrier (Goons Edition)
rig.description: The CAGE PLATE CARRIER (CPC) offers unrivaled comfort and load support in a low profile plate carrier configuration. The system supports a range of different pouches. In this case, the configuration is made by the leader of the Goons squad - Knight - for conducting assault operations with increased mobility.

rig.name: LBT-1961A Load Bearing Chest Rig (Goons Edition)
rig.description: A tactical load-bearing system designed to carry magazines, grenades, and special equipment, while using low-profile body armor. Manufactured by London Bridge Trading. Special configuration by Birdeye, member of the Goons squad.

rig.name: Tasmanian Tiger SK plate carrier (MultiCam Black)
rig.description: The ultra-light and skeletal TT Plate Carrier SK vest is made primarily from lightweight, thin and durable TPU-laminated Cordura nylon material with a claimed density of at least 700 denier. The design of the vest provides two lightweight covers for plates, adjustable shoulder straps and a light waist jumper. Equipped with a front panel for 4 magazines.

rig.name: NPP KlASS Bagariy plate carrier (EMR)
rig.description: In the second millennium, the equipment of a soldier received serious changes in view of new threats and tasks. A better level of protection was required, so the Russian army needed a reliable and functional body armor. In the mid-2000s, the MVD, which was later reorganized into the Russian Guard, received Bagariy bulletproof vests. Bagariy was used both by ordinary soldiers of the internal troops, and in special forces. Actively was used by PMC BEAR as the main heavy body armor.

rig.name: ECLiPSE RBAV-AF plate carrier (Ranger Green)
rig.description: The BAE ECLiPSE RBAV (Releasable Body Armor Vest, Air Force) variant is designed specifically for the Guardian Angel Weapon System (USAF PJ) and contains several new features not found in other versions.

rig.name: Azimut SS "Khamelion" chest harness (Olive)
rig.description: A simple harness system with non-removable pouches designed for grenades and SVD sniper rifle magazines. Manufactured by Azimut SpetsSnaryazheniye. Olive version.

rig.name: Shellback Tactical Banshee plate carrier (A-TACS AU)
rig.description: The Banshee Rifle Plate Carrier was designed to meet and exceed the needs of law enforcement, military, and tactical operators. This ultra lightweight, low profile, high-quality plate carrier has great load carrying capacity.

rig.name: WARTECH TV-115 plate carrier (Olive Drab)
rig.description: Operational armor system TV-115 with high-density polyethylene (class 3) plates, protecting only the chest and the back. Manufactured by WARTECH.

rig.name: Eagle Allied Industries MBSS plate carrier (Coyote Brown)
rig.description: The MBSS vest is part of the Maritime Ballistic Survivor System. The vest can be used with flotation inserts to provide buoyancy as it is not equipped with a quick release system. Manufactured by Eagle Allied Industries.

rig.name: Zulu Nylon Gear M4 Reduced Signature Chest Rig (Ranger Green)
rig.description: The M4 RSCR chest system was designed to be a lightweight and minimalist system for carrying just the essentials. Manufactured by Zulu Nylon Gear.

rig.name: Type 56 Chicom chest harness
rig.description: The Type 56 Chicom vest is the forefather of modern tactical loadout harness systems. The Type 56 rifle magazine chest harness was developed for the People's Liberation Army of China in the 1950s and has since been widely used in many local conflicts of the 20th century. In the early 1980s, such harnesses made their way to Afghanistan, where they gained acceptance by select Soviet troops who used the trophy Chicoms. It is unknown whether or not the Chicom served as a prototype for the Soviet Belt-A chest rig or not.

rig.name: Stich Profi Stich Defense mod.2 plate carrier (MultiCam)
rig.description: A plate carrier designed for Granit and SAPI plates, made of heavy-duty materials with IR remission. Equipped with ROC buckles for quick donning and doffing. The inner sides are made of soft fabric and equipped with vent pads for increased comfort. Manufactured by Stich Profi. MultiCam camouflage version.

rig.name: Tasmanian Tiger Plate Carrier MKIII (Coyote Brown)
rig.description: A lightweight low-profile plate carrier designed to fit SAPI plates. Manufactured by Tasmanian Tiger. Coyote Brown version.

rig.name: Stich Profi Plate Carrier V2 (Black)
rig.description: An improved lightweight version of the standard plate carrier manufactured by Stich Profi. Black color version.

rig.name: Spiritus Systems Bank Robber chest rig (MultiCam Alpine)
rig.description: An ultra-compact and lightweight chest rig for mobility and comfort. Manufactured by Spiritus Systems. MultiCam Alpine camouflage version, for all your winter LARP needs.

backpack.name: Flyye MBSS backpack (UCP)
backpack.description: An extra durable backpack made from 1000D Cordura with a separate pocket for a water bladder and a MOLLE attachment system on the sides.

backpack.name: Camelbak Tri-Zip assault backpack (Foliage)
backpack.description: A Mid-sized versatile assault pack. Spacious, sturdy and comfortable, this backpack is loved both by military and hikers worldwide. 34L of total space, a hydration system, easy access to side pockets, near-perfect suspension, and a MOLLE attachment system make it a great choice for up to 72 hours of autonomous hiking... or carrying a good load of loot.

backpack.name: Scav backpack
backpack.description: A cheap replica of some 3-day assault pack with a MOLLE attachment system, adapted and enhanced by the owner as much as their creativity allowed. Does not offer much comfort, and volume is far lower than that of a proper 3-day pack, but it's still a backpack alright.

backpack.name: Duffle bag
backpack.description: A gym duffle bag, generally seen before with fitness enthusiasts or long-distance commuters, is now a typical Scav attribute.

backpack.name: Transformer Bag
backpack.description: A rather spacious messenger bag, large enough to fit a lunchbox, laptop and some papers - or a small emergency survival kit. Its transformable sling and universal size allow it to be worn both as bag and a compact backpack.

backpack.name: Pilgrim tourist backpack
backpack.description: A large and brightly colored backpack that is perfect for the tourist on a raid.

backpack.name: SSO Attack 2 raid backpack (Khaki)
backpack.description: The 60-liter Ataka 2 ("Attack 2") raid backpack is intended for carrying personal belongings and equipment through tough field conditions.

backpack.name: VKBO army bag
backpack.description: Included in the all-season basic equipment kit (VKBO). Designed for transportation and storage of personal items of soldiers.

backpack.name: Tactical sling bag (Khaki)
backpack.description: An original sling bag for everyday wear or for active rest.

backpack.name: ANA Tactical Beta 2 Battle backpack (Olive Drab)
backpack.description: A lightweight and capacious backpack from ANA Tactical. Specially designed for use in dynamic conditions and on rough terrain.

backpack.name: Mystery Ranch Blackjack 50 backpack (MultiCam)
backpack.description: A backpack made for long and successful raids, manufactured by Mystery Ranch.

backpack.name: 3V Gear Paratus 3-Day Operator's Tactical backpack (Foliage Grey)
backpack.description: A modular, PVC-backed, polyester backpack for PMC operators who are going to be traversing across the rugged terrain of the Norvinsk region.

backpack.name: WARTECH Berkut BB-102 backpack (A-TACS FG)
backpack.description: A tactical backpack with front loading capabilities. Suitable for use by military and security forces, or for military tactical games. Manufactured in WARTECH.

backpack.name: Oakley Mechanism heavy duty backpack (Black)
backpack.description: The Mechanism backpack offers versatility and durable construction that accommodates any adventure. Heavy-duty metal clips, zips, and hook-and-loop closures create secure storage, and a flap-top opening means more room for hauling larger items. A variety of specialized pockets deliver military-style organization and easy access, and padded adjustable shoulder straps keep every excursion comfortable.

backpack.name: 6Sh118 raid backpack (EMR)
backpack.description: The 6Sh118 raid backpack is part of the 2nd generation "Ratnik" gear kit for combat. The 6Sh118 tactical army backpack is a modernization of the 6B38 Permyachka model raid backpack. The raid 6Sh118 backpack is designed to carry fire support equipment, weapons, ammunition, elements of mountain equipment, as well as the personal belongings of individual soldiers. The backpack can be used during combat operations, long hikes, and raid events.

backpack.name: LBT-2670 Slim Field Med Pack (Black)
backpack.description: A low-profile medical backpack, designed to carry large amounts of specialized medical equipment and supplies. Manufactured by London Bridge Trading.

backpack.name: Sanitar's bag
backpack.description: A medical bag, often used by mid and low rank medical personnel, sometimes by doctors, for carrying tools and medicine.

backpack.name: LBT-8005A Day Pack backpack (MultiCam Black)
backpack.description: A simple and reliable 14-liter backpack in MultiCam Black camouflage. Manufactured by London Bridge Trading.

backpack.name: LolKek 3F Transfer tourist backpack
backpack.description: A simple and cheap backpack manufactured by LolKek. Not very strong or comfortable, but it manages to carry loot in it, and that's all you need from a backpack.

backpack.name: Eberlestock F5 Switchblade backpack (Dry Earth)
backpack.description: A modern, high-quality, low-profile backpack for combat missions in all conditions.

backpack.name: Eberlestock F4 Terminator load bearing backpack (Tiger Stripe)
backpack.description: An extremely versatile full-format load bearing backpack for military use. Manufactured by Eberlestock.

backpack.name: Hazard 4 Takedown sling backpack (Black)
backpack.description: A single-strap sling backpack designed for carrying long-barreled weapons. Additional external pockets are designed to carry magazines, cleaning kit, or extra parts. Manufactured by Hazard 4. Black version.

backpack.name: Eberlestock G2 Gunslinger II backpack (Dry Earth)
backpack.description: The G2 is a mid-sized pack with a full-width scabbard to better accommodate weapons with larger cross-sections or bulky optics. The wide scabbard also allows it to serve as an excellent laptop or military radio compartment, and because it's also wide at the bottom, users have the option of carrying weapons butt-down or butt-up. Manufactured by Eberlestock.

backpack.name: Hazard 4 Takedown sling backpack (MultiCam)
backpack.description: A single-strap sling backpack designed for carrying long-barreled weapons. Additional external pockets are designed to carry magazines, cleaning kit, or extra parts. Manufactured by Hazard 4. MultiCam camouflage version.

backpack.name: Hazard 4 Drawbridge backpack (Coyote Tan)
backpack.description: Drawbridge is an ergonomical medium-size 25L backpack with an impressive amount of modular pouches and straps. Manufactured by Hazard 4.

backpack.name: Hazard 4 Pillbox backpack (Black)
backpack.description: A compact backpack for safe storage of fragile items, electronics and other valuables. Military modular webbing (MOLLE) is provided throughout on the sides, straps, and interior along with velcro panels to allow expansion with pouches, velcro i.d. patches, etc. Manufactured by Hazard 4.

backpack.name: Gruppa 99 T20 backpack (Umber Brown)
backpack.description: A backpack with a volume of 22 liters with an ergonomic harness for time-limited tasks. The backpack can be used for both operational tasks and urban carry. With proper packing, the inner volume of the backpack can be 25-27 liters. The minimalistic design and military functionality will be useful in urban environments. Manufactured by Gruppa 99. Umber Brown version.

backpack.name: LBT-1476A 3Day Pack (Woodland)
backpack.description: A medium-size 3-day backpack designed for both military and tourist use. Manufactured by London Bridge Trading.

backpack.name: Gruppa 99 T20 backpack (MultiCam)
backpack.description: A backpack with a volume of 22 liters with an ergonomic harness for time-limited tasks. The backpack can be used for both operational tasks and urban carry. With proper packing, the inner volume of the backpack can be 25-27 liters. The minimalistic design and military functionality will be useful in urban environments. Manufactured by Gruppa 99. MultiCam camouflage version.

backpack.name: Santa's bag
backpack.description: A big and roomy Christmas bag, left behind by Santa himself.

backpack.name: Mystery Ranch NICE COMM 3 BVS frame system (Coyote)
backpack.description: The NICE Frame special system for carrying oversized or heavy loads with an installed COMM 3 backpack for carrying radio systems. The COMM 3 main bay is designed for PRC117F or G, PRC119F, 152, or ASIP radios. The Hitchhiker and Daypack lid allows you to carry separate gear if needed. The modular NICE COMM 3 system is ready to adapt to changing tasks. An extremely rare thing, for which a real hunt is conducted in Tarkov.

backpack.name: Gruppa 99 T30 backpack (Black)
backpack.description: A thirty-liter assault backpack from Gruppa 99. A high-quality solution for conducting special raid operations. Black version.

backpack.name: Gruppa 99 T30 backpack (MultiCam)
backpack.description: A thirty-liter assault backpack from Gruppa 99. A high-quality solution for conducting special raid operations. MultiCam camouflage version.

backpack.name: Tasmanian Tiger Trooper 35 backpack (Khaki)
backpack.description: The TT Trooper Light Pack 35 is a lightweight and functional 35 liter backpack from Tasmanian Tiger with a comfortable and ergonomic PaddenBack suspension system and anatomical shoulder straps.

backpack.name: Tehinkom RK-PT-25 patrol backpack (EMR)
backpack.description: This backpack is a multifunctional piece of equipment designed for transportation of various items of combat and marching equipment, additional weaponry, etc. It can be used both as part of the UMTBS transportation and gear system (ZhTU 6Sh112) and independently, as part of various sets of individual combat equipment.

backpack.name: Mystery Ranch SATL Bridger Assault Pack (Foliage)
backpack.description: The Mystery Ranch SATL assault backpack has been the standard gear for SOCOM assault operations for nearly a decade. It now features a removable BVS system and a redirect waist belt for effective weight distribution, even when the backpack is worn over body armor.

backpack.name: Direct Action Dragon Egg Mark II backpack (Black)
backpack.description: A lightweight and versatile backpack with a volume of over 25 liters, designed for military and law enforcement personnel.

backpack.name: Partisan's bag
backpack.description: An old used Gorka bag. It seems that Partisan replaced his old Afghan trophies with patches of PMC operatives who were foolish enough to cross him in some way when they came to Tarkov.

backpack.name: Camelbak Tri-Zip assault backpack (MultiCam)
backpack.description: A Mid-sized versatile assault pack. Spacious, sturdy and comfortable, this backpack is loved both by military and hikers worldwide. 34L of total space, a hydration system, easy access to side pockets, near-perfect suspension, and a MOLLE attachment system make it a great choice for up to 72 hours of autonomous hiking... or carrying a good load of loot. MultiCam camouflage version.

backpack.name: Vertx Ready Pack backpack (Red)
backpack.description: A tactical (but not overly tactical) everyday carry 20L backpack made by Vertx. Red color version.

backpack.name: 5.11 Tactical RUSH 100 backpack (Black)
backpack.description: A tactical backpack with a complex modular system. The arrangement of internal compartments and side straps makes the RUSH 100 a highly versatile backpack that can be adapted to any combat situation.

backpack.name: LBT-1476A 3Day Pack (MultiCam Alpine)
backpack.description: A medium-size 3-day backpack designed for both military and tourist use. Manufactured by London Bridge Trading. MultiCam Alpine version.

backpack.name: Mystery Ranch Terraframe backpack (Olive Drab)
backpack.description: A comfortable and spacious backpack for its volume, it remained popular even in wartime. Judging by the attached antlers, this backpack used to belong to a hunter.

backpack.name: Mystery Ranch Terraframe backpack (Christmas Edition)
backpack.description: Someone has decorated the standard Terraframe model for Christmas. The weight hasn't changed much, but going into a raid has become somehow... more cheerful?

meds.name: Aseptic bandage
meds.description: The most common gauze bandage, autoclaved and aseptic.

meds.name: Immobilizing splint
meds.description: A common splint for fixing damaged bones in place.

meds.name: Analgin painkillers
meds.description: The cheapest and most widely available Metamizole painkillers.

meds.name: Morphine injector
meds.description: A single-use syringe full of morphine. A powerful drug, used primarily to treat both acute and chronic severe pain.

meds.name: Salewa first aid kit
meds.description: A first aid kit containing a bivibag, various types of bandages, and dressing tools.

meds.name: Army bandage
meds.description: An army-issue gauze bandage.

meds.name: Golden Star balm
meds.description: The famous Vietnamese "Golden Star" balm, also known as Cao Sao Vang, is made from essential oils like Camphor, Menthol, Peppermint, Cajuput, all mixed into vaseline. A small amount of the balm is applied to the sub-district and rubbing of the skin: for headache - the temples and the nape of the neck, with a cold - under the nostrils, the common cold - in the chest, back, abdomen, insect bites - on the place of bite. External use only!

meds.name: AI-2 medkit
meds.description: The AI-2 medkit was developed as a standard service first aid kit for various defense and law enforcement agencies and civil defense forces of USSR. In case of all-out conflict with the use of weapons of mass destruction it should have been distributed to the population of the affected and surrounding areas.

meds.name: Vaseline balm
meds.description: Vaseline, or, more precisely, petroleum jelly, is a versatile ointment used for a number of purposes where its water insulation and lubrication properties are required, for instance, for treating small cuts and burns, coating corrosion-prone items or lubricating gear that requires non-acidic lubricants.

meds.name: Grizzly medical kit
meds.description: Sportsman Series Grizzly Medical Kit is considered one of the best first aid kits. It contains everything necessary to provide immediate medical care in extreme conditions.

meds.name: Car first aid kit
meds.description: Like a fire extinguisher, car first aid kit is crucially important protection measure in the event of an emergency on the road.

meds.name: IFAK individual first aid kit
meds.description: IFAK is a personal medical kit issued to soldiers in service. The official first aid kit in the U.S. Marine Corps IFAK (Individual First Aid Kit of the United States Marine Corps). The latest, third-generation (gen3), the most well-designed and rich in contents.

meds.name: Augmentin antibiotic pills
meds.description: Augmentin is a complex versatile antibiotic used to treat bacterial infections.

meds.name: Aluminum splint
meds.description: An aluminum splint for fixing damaged bones in place.

meds.name: Ibuprofen painkillers
meds.description: Ibuprofen is a medication in the nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) class that is used for treating pain, fever, and inflammation.

meds.name: Propital regenerative stimulant injector
meds.description: A military-issue stimulant permitted to only be used by medical officers and paramedics. It stimulates regeneration processes by increasing the biosynthesis of purine and pyrimidine bases, RNA, functional, and enzymatic cell elements. Increases metabolism, health, and vitality. Has continuous side effects.

meds.name: SJ1 TGLabs combat stimulant injector
meds.description: A combat stimulant. It is used for gaining strength and endurance before combat. Decreases sensation of pain. Stimulant is allowed to use by the special forces units. Developed by TerraGroup Labs, marked as SJ1. Has side effects.

meds.name: SJ6 TGLabs combat stimulant injector
meds.description: A combat stimulant. It is used to increase the body abilities before combat. Stimulant is allowed to use by the special forces units. Developed by TerraGroup Labs, marked as SJ6. Has side effects.

meds.name: Zagustin hemostatic drug injector
meds.description: A military-issue drug. Inhibits activators of profibrinolysin and slows down its transformation in fibrinolysin. Temporarily stops the bleeding and increases resistance to bloodloss. Has side effects. Leads to severe dehydration.

meds.name: eTG-change regenerative stimulant injector
meds.description: A powerful stimulant for regeneration processes. It is used for rapid recovery of a soldier after injury, or during transportation of heavily wounded personnel. Allowed to be used only by medical officers and paramedics. Has strong side effects.

meds.name: Adrenaline injector
meds.description: A sterile disposable syringe with a dose of adrenaline - the main hormone of the adrenal medulla. It is used to enhance the physiological response associated with the preparation of all muscles to increased activity. Temporarily boosts strength and endurance. Relieves the sensation of pain.

meds.name: CMS surgical kit
meds.description: Compact surgical kit for treatment of bullet wounds and other serious injuries.

meds.name: Surv12 field surgical kit
meds.description: An advanced surgical kit with additional high-quality tools, allowing treating serious injuries right on the battlefield.

meds.name: Esmarch tourniquet
meds.description: The hemostatic tourniquet is named after Friedrich August von Esmarch, who proposed its use, along with other methods in military field surgery.

meds.name: CALOK-B hemostatic applicator
meds.description: The CALOK-B applicator hemostatic agent allows you to inject hemostatic granules through a wound opening directly to the source of bleeding in just a few seconds.

meds.name: 3-(b-TG) stimulant injector
meds.description: Combat drug. It has a stimulating effect on the Central nervous system. Increases perception and attention. It can slightly improve strength indicators, due to more powerful signals to the muscles. The active substance is 3-(b-Phenylisopropyl)-sydnonimine hydrochloride. Allowed for use only by military doctors and paramedics.

meds.name: L1 (Norepinephrine) injector
meds.description: A sterile disposable syringe with a dose of L1, based on norepinephrine. It is used for short-term increase of strength and endurance, as well as to reduce the pain effect. This activates the implementation of a physiological response such as "hit or run". Increases water and energy consumption.

meds.name: P22 (Product 22) stimulant injector
meds.description: A combat stimulant. Developed by TerraGroup Labs, marked as P22. It allows the tissues of the body to receive less damage when physically exposed due to passive inclusion in the work of internal muscles. It is used to expand the body's abilities before a fight. Authorized for use by special forces soldiers. Has side effects.

meds.name: AHF1-M stimulant injector
meds.description: A military drug based on human antihemophilic factor. Developed by TerraGroup Labs as a powerful coagulant specifically for USEC operatives. Temporarily stops bleeding and increases resistance to new ones. Slightly improves health indicators, leads to dehydration.

meds.name: Meldonin injector
meds.description: A drug developed for athletes. Allows conducting more intensive training and recovering stamina faster. Temporarily increases strength, endurance,and also accelerates recovery. An undocumented property was also found: it increases the resistance of tissues to physical impact due to internal muscle tension. Because of its properties, it was later adopted by the military as a combat stimulant. Has side effects.

meds.name: M.U.L.E. stimulant injector
meds.description: Muscular Ultra Large Exciter. It is used to expand the body's abilities before long marches. It allows the body to carry an increased weight for a long time. It has shown effectiveness in combat operations in areas where transport is not available. Authorized for use by special forces soldiers. Developed by TerraGroup Labs, marked with the name M. U. L. E.

meds.name: Obdolbos cocktail injector
meds.description: A syringe with a homemade drug, authored by a former employee of TerraGroup Labs. The negative effects are different each time. You could take the risk, got nothing to lose anyway.

meds.name: xTG-12 antidote injector
meds.description: Removes most of the known poisons and toxins used in the combat industry. Can be used to relieve the effects of natural poisons. Gives immunity to poisoning while the components are in the blood system. Can reduce health status.

meds.name: SJ9 TGLabs combat stimulant injector
meds.description: Designed for special forces personnel. It makes it possible to reduce the human body temperature for a short time, significantly slowing down the metabolism. The use of SJ9 leads to a significant reduction in the amount of heat released into the environment, while maintaining a safe level of metabolism inside. It is used during night operations, allowing to be hardly visible for thermal imaging devices.

meds.name: AFAK tactical individual first aid kit
meds.description: AFAK (Adaptive First Aid Kit). A more advanced version of the IFAK individual first aid kit. The compact kit provides the individual soldier or law enforcement officer with a necessary lifesaving equipment to effectively treat injuries commonly associated with combat trauma.

meds.name: CAT hemostatic tourniquet
meds.description: CAT (Combat Application Tourniquet) prevents blood loss by blocking the blood outlet by applying pressure to the affected limb. It uses a self-adjusting tensioning system and a tug-resistant buckle.

meds.name: Obdolbos 2 cocktail injector
meds.description: A syringe with a homemade drug, developed by Sanitar. A new version of the old classic. Looks like TerraGroup Labs' experiments did not end with the closure of TerraGroup Labs itself.

meds.name: SJ12 TGLabs combat stimulant injector
meds.description: Developed for the operatives of special units. Slows down some functions of the body and they temporarily start working with energy regeneration. The drug forces the release of vasopressin in the hypothalamus, which leads to a change in the work of the adrenal glands, lowers body temperature and increases perception. After the end of the action, there is usually a jump in temperature to 40-42 degrees as a compensation for the incorrect functioning of the body systems.

meds.name: PNB (Product 16) stimulant injector
meds.description: A combat stimulant. Developed by TerraGroup Labs, labeled PNB. Allows a short-term activation of the inner muscles, bringing them into a state of hypertonicity, which in turn reduces the received damage. At the same time there is an active synthesis of proteins for accelerated tissue regeneration. Used for the expansion of the organism abilities at the key moment of the combat. Allowed for use by Special Forces. Has some side effects.

meds.name: Trimadol stimulant injector
meds.description: An opioid synthetic analgesic developed for special forces operatives. It has a central and spinal cord action (promotes opening of K+ and Ca2+ channels, causes hyperpolarization of membranes and inhibits conduction of pain impulses). In addition to the analgesic effect, it increases combat characteristics. Overdose leads to exhaustion of the body after the effects wear off.

meds.name: Perfotoran (Blue Blood) stimulant injector
meds.description: A blood substitute with the function of oxygen transfer, used as a powerful antidote capable of relieving toxins, poisons, and radiation damage. It was developed by Soviet scientists in the 1980s. It is a submicron emulsion based on PFO compounds. Once in the blood, it temporarily speeds up the metabolism and regenerates tissues. Negatively affects health in case of overdose or rejection.

meds.name: 2A2-(b-TG) stimulant injector
meds.description: TerraGroup's next development after the 3-(b-TG) stimulant. The goal of the project was to obtain a drug that would give an advantage in reconnaissance and crossing combat zones far away from supply points. At the same time, the drug is required to be manufacturable in handicraft conditions. The obtained substance allows to keep the CNS in tone for a long period of time, which positively affects the fighter's efficiency to assess the environment, and also enhances their ability to carry equipment. The stimulant’s effective duration is accompanied by increased loss of hydration.

injectors.name: Morphine injector
injectors.description: A single-use syringe full of morphine. A powerful drug, used primarily to treat both acute and chronic severe pain.

injectors.name: Propital regenerative stimulant injector
injectors.description: A military-issue stimulant permitted to only be used by medical officers and paramedics. It stimulates regeneration processes by increasing the biosynthesis of purine and pyrimidine bases, RNA, functional, and enzymatic cell elements. Increases metabolism, health, and vitality. Has continuous side effects.

injectors.name: SJ1 TGLabs combat stimulant injector
injectors.description: A combat stimulant. It is used for gaining strength and endurance before combat. Decreases sensation of pain. Stimulant is allowed to use by the special forces units. Developed by TerraGroup Labs, marked as SJ1. Has side effects.

injectors.name: SJ6 TGLabs combat stimulant injector
injectors.description: A combat stimulant. It is used to increase the body abilities before combat. Stimulant is allowed to use by the special forces units. Developed by TerraGroup Labs, marked as SJ6. Has side effects.

injectors.name: Zagustin hemostatic drug injector
injectors.description: A military-issue drug. Inhibits activators of profibrinolysin and slows down its transformation in fibrinolysin. Temporarily stops the bleeding and increases resistance to bloodloss. Has side effects. Leads to severe dehydration.
