barter.name: Leatherman Multitool
barter.description: With this compact and versatile multitool there is no need to be worried about having no tools on you at the right time.

barter.name: 40mm VOG-25 grenade
barter.description: A 40mm VOG-25 underbarrel grenade launcher fragmentation round with an arming distance of 25-30 meters.

barter.name: AA Battery
barter.description: An AA Battery, used over a wide array of consumer devices.

barter.name: D Size battery
barter.description: D (also R20, 373, Mono, UM) - one of the standard sizes for multipurpose batteries, used in the most energy-consuming portable electric devices like portable stereos, radiosets, GM counters, and powerful hand lights.

barter.name: Geiger-Muller counter
barter.description: A gas discharge device for an automatic count of detected ionizing particles.

barter.name: Crickent lighter
barter.description: A regular gas lighter, manufactured by Crickent.

barter.name: Zibbo lighter
barter.description: A metal gasoline Zibbo lighter, renowned for being reliable and windproof.

barter.name: Broken GPhone smartphone
barter.description: GPhone 9s - one of the previous generations of the famous smartphone model. Shattered beyond repair.

barter.name: Car battery
barter.description: Typical 12 V, 51 Ah lead-acid car batteries are in a big demand with traders, who resell them in the areas that have been left without power supply.

barter.name: Chainlet
barter.description: A small piece of jewelry worn around the neck. Depending on the materials and weight, can be quite valuable even now.

barter.name: Golden neck chain
barter.description: A golden neck chain is bound to be a rather profitable piece of jewelry to find.

barter.name: Apollo Soyuz cigarettes
barter.description: Apollo Soyuz cigarettes. Inhaling those will potentially make you cough up to the stars in your eyes.

barter.name: Malboro Cigarettes
barter.description: Malboro Cigarettes are a big hit with the wealthier part of the local smoking populace.

barter.name: Wilston cigarettes
barter.description: The image of a typical street punk would not be complete without Wilston cigarettes.

barter.name: Strike Cigarettes
barter.description: Strike Cigarettes can be sold off to traders for their personal use later.

barter.name: CPU fan
barter.description: In conditions of total deficiency of elementary goods and conveniences, CPU cooling fans come in handy for crafty locals - wind power generators made from them charge radios, they are used as household fans, and even serve as vent intakes, replacing native heavy blades.

barter.name: PC CPU
barter.description: PC central processing units, in lack of properly working computers, have found their purpose as a construction material for makeshift antenna reflector-type parasites.

barter.name: DVD drive
barter.description: Magnets, laser diodes, and lenses make PC DVD drives a valuable resource for all sorts of makeshift survivor geekery, including motion detectors and designators.

barter.name: Horse figurine
barter.description: A horrendously kitsch horse figurine is useless in Tarkov - just as anywhere else - but somewhere out there, there are dealers still willing to buy such things. Something is not right about this.

barter.name: Insulating tape
barter.description: Although insulating tape is primarily intended for insulation of wires, its practical application is limited only by the creativity of its owner. Most typical cases include minor maintenance, holding together split parts, binding some stuff together and anti-slip wrapping of handles.

barter.name: Classic matches
barter.description: A matchbox full of safety matches. Lighters are more reliable and easier to use, but that's exactly why everybody tries to keep them hidden when asked for a light.

barter.name: RAM stick
barter.description: Old RAM is a primary source of IC chips for various microcontroller purposes of the local population.

barter.name: Duct tape
barter.description: Duct tape is a universal tool to fix in one place something that moves, but shouldn't.

barter.name: Power supply unit
barter.description: A PC power supply unit can be easily converted from powering PCs to a universal charger for all kinds of low-voltage rechargeable batteries and devices.

barter.name: Bolts
barter.description: Bolts, together with screw nuts, are used to fasten things in place. An essential item for organizing a Hideout.

barter.name: Screw nuts
barter.description: Just a handful of commonplace screw nuts, with no apparent use. An essential item for organizing a Hideout.

barter.name: Toothpaste
barter.description: Not that teeth hygiene is so essential in the city these days, but why not, if a chance is here.

barter.name: Graphics card
barter.description: A graphics card is just as good a source of electronic components as anything else - fans, CPUs, IC, etc.

barter.name: T-Shaped plug
barter.description: A T-shaped splitter adapter for the wall power outlet.

barter.name: Factory plan map
barter.description: A simplified and updated copy of the Chemical Plant No. 16 facility blueprint.

barter.name: Printer paper
barter.description: Office-grade paper for printers and copiers, it can nevertheless be used for writing as well, just like any paper.

barter.name: Simple wallet
barter.description: A simple wallet for storing money.

barter.name: Customs plan map
barter.description: A paper plan map of the vast Customs premises. Not the most up-to-date copy, but it's better than nothing.

barter.name: Woods plan map
barter.description: A paper plan map of Priozersk Natural Reserve.

barter.name: USB Adapter
barter.description: A battery charger with a USB output. Used to be an indispensable household item.

barter.name: Rechargeable battery
barter.description: A chemical source of electric current, reusable source of voltage, characterized by the reversibility of internal chemical processes that ensures its repeated cyclic use (via charge-discharge) for energy accumulation and autonomous power supply of various electrical devices and equipment, as well as providing backup power sources in medicine, manufacturing and other areas.

barter.name: Dry fuel
barter.description: Dry fuel - in household use it is commonly referred to as dry alcohol. Dry fuel consists of urotropine pressed with a small amount of wax. Typically used for heating or cooking food in field conditions by tourists, military and rescue organizations.

barter.name: Damaged hard drive
barter.description: A random access storage device (information storage device), based on the magnetic recording principle. Serves as the main data drive in most computers. Hardware specialists use broken disks to salvage the controllers and magnets for re-use in other electronics.

barter.name: Magnet
barter.description: A handcrafted magnet. It's extremely rare, considering the total deficit of working electronics and parts for electric motors.

barter.name: Printed circuit board
barter.description: A universal component in microelectronics. An essential resource for maintaining electronic systems.

barter.name: Spark plug
barter.description: Spark plugs are used for gasoline internal combustion engines. Ignition of the fuel-air mixture is produced by electric discharge with a voltage of several thousand or tens of thousands of volts, emerging between the electrodes. The plug fires on each round, at one point of the engine operating cycle.

barter.name: Energy-saving lamp
barter.description: An electric lamp with substantially greater luminous efficiency (the ratio of luminous flux and power consumption), for example, in comparison with filament lamps which are still rather common. Thanks to that, the replacement of incandescent light bulbs with energy-saving ones saves energy, protecting the environment.

barter.name: Ultraviolet lamp
barter.description: A UV lamp for household use is a type of light bulb which source of light is invisible to the human eye, located on the border of the purple spectrum and x-ray radiation. UV radiation has beneficial effects on all the systems of human and animal bodies, contributing to the development of a strong defensive system against viral and infectious diseases, such as seasonal colds.

barter.name: Gas analyzer
barter.description: A measuring device for determining the qualitative and quantitative composition of gas mixtures. It has a very wide range of applications - in environmental protection, internal combustion engines management systems, and medicine.

barter.name: Pliers
barter.description: A tool for capturing, manipulating, and cutting wire.

barter.name: Construction measuring tape
barter.description: A tool designed to measure length. Indispensable in construction and renovation.

barter.name: Screwdriver
barter.description: A manual bench work tool designed for screwing and unscrewing threaded fasteners, most commonly screws that have spline on their heads. Usually it’s a metal rod with a tip and grip (plastic or wood).

barter.name: Toolset
barter.description: A repairman’s bag with a set of different tools.

barter.name: Wrench
barter.description: A twin-head wrench. Despite the simplicity of design, the wrench is used in almost all areas of technology to build mechanisms of various levels of difficulty.

barter.name: Pack of nails
barter.description: A package of construction nails. In conditions of continuing crisis they are used for construction of temporary shelters, bunkhouses, and other assembly.

barter.name: Xenomorph sealing foam
barter.description: Xenomorph is a sealing foam with an excellent structure of cells and high mechanical strength. Easy to use, applied with a thin applicator tube. Foam is an expandable material that doubles its volume on solidification. Has excellent adhesion to most building materials such as wood, concrete, stone, metal, etc. This product does not contain any chloro-fluoro-carbon propellants. A reliable and cost-effective solution for sealing and filling the voids.

barter.name: Shustrilo sealing foam
barter.description: Shustrilo is a professional premium sealing foam for use with a foam pistol. Distinguished by high output of foam from a cylinder, improved parameters of strength, stability, etc. Highest quality of Shustrilo products ensures guaranteed work results.

barter.name: SAS drive
barter.description: A reinforced case with an SAS hard drive. Used for data storage in military industry.

barter.name: SSD drive
barter.description: A solid state drive. Used to store data with enhanced read and write performance.

barter.name: Gas mask air filter
barter.description: The GP-7k FPK filter in a metal case for the GP-7 gas mask.

barter.name: Gunpowder "Kite"
barter.description: A tin with gunpowder. An essential resource for creating weapon cartridges. The composition of the Kite gunpowder is distinguished by the use of pyroxylin with presence of graphite, which is necessary to reduce the electrification of the mixture.

barter.name: WD-40 (100ml)
barter.description: Initially, this agent was developed for industrial consumers as an anti-corrosive water repellent. It was later discovered that it also had plenty of domestic use applications. According to the legend, the product's formula was developed on the fortieth attempt (WD-40 as short for Water Displacement - 40th Attempt). The product consists mostly of various hydrocarbons.

barter.name: WD-40 (400ml)
barter.description: Initially, this agent was developed for industrial consumers as an anti-corrosive water repellent. It was later discovered that it also had plenty of domestic use applications. According to legend, the product's formula was developed on the fortieth attempt (WD-40 as short for Water Displacement-40th Attempt). The product consists mostly of various hydrocarbons.

barter.name: Secure Flash drive
barter.description: A secure flash drive. Such USB sticks are frequently used by TerraGroup employees. They can definitely contain sensitive data.

barter.name: Tech manual
barter.description: A manual with technical documentation.

barter.name: Diary
barter.description: A diary with a leather cover. Covered with various names, addresses and phone numbers. Somebody might find it particularly useful.

barter.name: Slim diary
barter.description: A diary with a leather cover. Covered with various names, addresses and phone numbers. Somebody might find it particularly useful.

barter.name: Antique teapot
barter.description: An item from a rare collection of antique silver tea service set.

barter.name: Antique vase
barter.description: A porcelain vase from a private collection. In theory, can serve as a beer pitcher.

barter.name: MS2000 Marker
barter.description: A strobe marker light that is used during nighttime operations. It emits signals in the IR region which are visible through NVGs. Uses a special filter when operating in the IR mode. If the filter is removed, it appears as a bright flash in the visible spectrum. In the extended mode operates with a blue flash.

barter.name: Ox bleach
barter.description: The "Ox" special bleach and stain remover. The bleaching agent destroys chemical bonds, which is actively used in chemical production.

barter.name: Clin window cleaner
barter.description: The "Clin" window cleaner fluid. Actively used in home-made chemical production.

barter.name: PAID AntiRoach spray
barter.description: Tactical combat spray for annihilating cockroaches and ants. An indispensable thing for Hideout maintenance.

barter.name: Pack of sodium bicarbonate
barter.description: An acidic salt of carbonic acid and sodium. It is usually a fine-grained white powder. Used in the food industry, cooking, or medicine as a neutralizer of skin burns and mucous membranes of human acids and reducing the acidity of gastric juice.

barter.name: Corrugated hose
barter.description: Corrugated hose for use in gardens. Could be useful for organizing a Hideout.

barter.name: Electric drill
barter.description: A cordless electric drill. Used in construction, furniture installation, and repair.

barter.name: Pack of screws
barter.description: A self-tapping screw is a fastening product in the form of a rod with a head and a special external thread that forms an internal thread in the hole of the object to be connected. Used for the installation of wooden, plasterboard, and plastic panels.

barter.name: Bottle of saline solution
barter.description: Physiological saline solution, whose osmotic pressure is equal to the osmotic pressure of the blood. There are several types of physiological solutions, the composition of which depends on the purposes for which they are applied.

barter.name: Bottle of hydrogen peroxide
barter.description: Hydrogen peroxide is used in medicine as a cleaning and antiseptic treatment for wounds.

barter.name: Bronze lion figurine
barter.description: A collectible bronze lion figure. The thing is heavy, seemingly beautiful. Useful either for sale or aesthetic pleasure.

barter.name: Wooden clock
barter.description: Extremely artfully made wooden clock in the form of a two-headed eagle. A rare and expensive thing.

barter.name: Cat figurine
barter.description: An antique statuette of a cat, made of a rare sort of wood called Makassar Ebony.

barter.name: Piece of plexiglass
barter.description: Organic glass is an acrylic resin, synthetic vinyl polymer of methyl methacrylate, thermoplastic transparent plastic, also known as plexiglass.

barter.name: Power cord
barter.description: An electrical 220v power cable for Personal Computers.

barter.name: Dogtag USEC
barter.description: Army dogtags serve the purpose of quickly identifying the wounded and deceased in combat. This one belonged to a USEC PMC operator.

barter.description: A gold watch of the famous Roler brand. The case is made of 18 karats yellow gold.

barter.name: Alkaline cleaner for heat exchangers
barter.description: Alkali is actively used to remove various deposits in pipes and heating elements. Also used in artisanal chemical production.

helmet.name: FORT Kiver-M bulletproof helmet
helmet.description: The FORT Kiver-M bulletproof helmets are designed for use by officers of special law enforcement agencies of the Russian Federation.

helmet.name: Kolpak-1S riot helmet
helmet.description: Kolpak-1S protects the head from the cold piercing-cutting weapons in a special class of protection GOST R50744-95, from fragmentation with an energy of impact up to 50 J, and also serves to reduce the dynamic loads arising from the above-mentioned means of destruction. Kolpak-1 protective helmets are recommended by the Interdepartmental Commission for equipping units of the patrol service, traffic police, OMON and other special units of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russia.

helmet.name: Jack-o'-lantern tactical pumpkin helmet
helmet.description: Jack-o'-lantern is here to protect you from the Evil.

helmet.name: Ops-Core FAST MT Super High Cut helmet (Black)
helmet.description: The Ops-Core FAST Maritime ballistic helmet is popular in special forces all around the world. Can be modified with different components. Black version.

helmet.name: 6B47 Ratnik-BSh helmet (Olive Drab)
helmet.description: 6B47 is an aramid helmet of Russian origin. As part of the Ratnik program, it is the new standard-issue helmet for most of the Russian Armed Forces. The 6B47 is similar to previous generation helmets such as the 6B7-1M and 6B27. It has equal protection but weighs slightly less, floats in water, and has mounting equipment for lights and night vision devices. The helmet can be fitted with a variety of covers for different environments.

helmet.name: 6B47 Ratnik-BSh helmet (EMR cover)
helmet.description: 6B47 is an aramid helmet of Russian origin. As part of the Ratnik program, it is the new standard-issue helmet for most of the Russian Armed Forces. The 6B47 is similar to previous generation helmets such as the 6B7-1M and 6B27. It has equal protection but weighs slightly less, floats in water, and has mounting equipment for lights and night vision devices. The helmet can be fitted with a variety of covers for different environments. Equipped with an EMR (Digital Flora) camouflage cover.

helmet.name: UNTAR helmet
helmet.description: A standard-issue helmet used by UN soldiers during the UNTAR mission in Tarkov.

helmet.name: SSSh-94 SFERA-S helmet
helmet.description: The SSSh-94 "SFERA-S" ("Special Steel Helmet 94 Sphere-S") is a special helmet with modular protection made with thickened armored steel. Used by special forces of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation.

helmet.name: Altyn bulletproof helmet (Olive Drab)
helmet.description: The "Altyn" helmets passed real combat tests in Afghanistan and Chechnya and are still in service with the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation and the army special forces. Can be equipped with an armored faceshield visor.

helmet.name: ZSh-1-2M helmet (Olive Drab)
helmet.description: The ZSh-1-2M helmet consists of a durable alloy covered from the inside by aramid fabrics which does not allow penetration of the protective layer and absorbs the dynamic impact of bullets or shrapnel.

helmet.name: ZSh-1-2M helmet (Black cover)
helmet.description: The ZSh-1-2M helmet consists of a durable alloy covered from the inside by aramid fabrics which does not allow penetration of the protective layer and absorbs the dynamic impact of bullets or shrapnel. Equipped with a black colored cover.

helmet.name: Ops-Core FAST MT Super High Cut helmet (Urban Tan)
helmet.description: The Ops-Core FAST Maritime ballistic helmet is popular in special forces all around the world. Can be modified with different components. Urban Tan version.

helmet.name: HighCom Striker ULACH IIIA helmet (Black)
helmet.description: A combat helmet with the ears and back of the head protection, manufactured by HighCom. Does not feature any additional mounts. Black version.

helmet.name: HighCom Striker ULACH IIIA helmet (Desert Tan)
helmet.description: A combat helmet with the ears and back of the head protection, manufactured by HighCom. Does not feature any additional mounts. Desert Tan version.

helmet.name: HighCom Striker ACHHC IIIA helmet (Black)
helmet.description: A combat helmet manufactured by HighCom, the High Cut version. Does not feature any additional mounts. Black version.

helmet.name: HighCom Striker ACHHC IIIA helmet (Olive Drab)
helmet.description: A combat helmet manufactured by HighCom, the High Cut version. Does not feature any additional mounts. Olive Drab version.

helmet.name: DevTac Ronin Respirator
helmet.description: A Japan-styled tactical helmet, manufactured by DevTac. Not used by any military or special forces. Just somehow happened to be in Tarkov for some frivolous price. Features a full NIJ level IIIA protection of the whole head, though you really don't want to get shot in the face with this thing.

helmet.name: Shattered lightweight armored mask
helmet.description: The "Shattered" face protection mask, reinforced with aramid fibers.

helmet.name: LShZ lightweight helmet (Olive Drab)
helmet.description: A lightweight protective helmet made in Russia. Basically a cheap copy of Ops-Core FAST helmet with lower characteristics.

helmet.name: SSh-68 steel helmet (Olive Drab)
helmet.description: SSh-68 replaced the general-army SSh-60 helmet. It differs from its predecessor in greater durability, a large inclination of the front part, and short side boards.

helmet.name: ShPM Firefighter helmet
helmet.description: Firefighter helmet is an individual means of fire protection and is designed to ensure the protection of the firefighter's head from exposure to elevated temperatures, mechanical shocks, corrosive environments and other dangerous and harmful factors arising from extinguishing fires and conducting emergency rescue operations.

helmet.name: Maska-1SCh bulletproof helmet (Olive Drab)
helmet.description: The Maska-1 bulletproof protective helmet appeared in service in 1991 as a replacement for the "Sphere" helmet, designed for use by the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation armed forces. The Maska-1SCh ("Mask-1 Shield") modification features a steel bulletproof faceshield to ensure maximum protection of the user's face.

helmet.name: PSh-97 DJETA riot helmet
helmet.description: The PSh-97 "DJETA" police helmet is designed to protect the head from being hit by heavy objects, metal rods, etc.

helmet.name: Maska-1SCh bulletproof helmet (Killa Edition)
helmet.description: The Maska-1 bulletproof protective helmet appeared in service in 1991 as a replacement for the "Sphere" helmet, designed for use by the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation armed forces. The Maska-1SCh ("Mask-1 Shield") modification features a bulletproof steel faceshield to ensure maximum protection of the user's face. This particular one is Killa's personal helmet, painted in black with three stylish vertical stripes.

helmet.name: Crye Precision AirFrame helmet (Tan)
helmet.description: The AirFrame ballistic helmet sets the standards in protection, comfort, and modularity. The unique overlapping shell design of the AirFrame creates an integrated vent that provides passive cooling and can reduce the damaging effects of explosive blast waves. Highly modular. Manufactured by Crye Precision.

helmet.name: Vulkan-5 LShZ-5 bulletproof helmet (Black)
helmet.description: The Vulkan-5 LShZ-5 high-level protection helmet is intended for use in a set of combat equipment with circular 5-class (Russian GOST) head protection from medium to heavy projectiles.

helmet.name: MSA ACH TC-2001 MICH Series helmet (Olive Drab)
helmet.description: The MSA Advanced Combat Helmet (ACH) delivers advanced ballistic, fragmentation, and impact head protection, with comfort for long-term use. The helmet’s low-profile design reduces the risk of interference in target acquisition and ensures compatibility with NVGs and headsets.

helmet.name: MSA ACH TC-2002 MICH Series helmet (Olive Drab)
helmet.description: The MSA Advanced Combat Helmet (ACH) delivers advanced ballistic, fragmentation, and impact head protection, with comfort for long-term use. The helmet’s low-profile design reduces the risk of interference in target acquisition and ensures compatibility with NVGs and headsets.

helmet.name: BNTI LShZ-2DTM helmet (Black)
helmet.description: The LShZ-2DTM helmet is intended for periodic wearing with the purpose of protection from bullets of small arms of a user’s head, as well as for protection from bullets of small arms of a user’s face and neck when equipped with a visor and aventail.

helmet.name: TSh-4M-L soft tank crew helmet
helmet.description: The TSh-4M-L(Z)-01 soft tank crew helmet with headset is designed to provide two-way radiotelephone communication in objects with a high level of noise, to protect it from climatic factors and from impacts on structural elements of objects.

helmet.name: Team Wendy EXFIL Ballistic Helmet (Black)
helmet.description: One of the most recent tactical ballistic helmets with extensive customization capabilities. The EXFIL LTP (Lightweight, Tactical, Polymer) bump helmet provides impact protection for maritime environments and a stable, comfortable platform for mounting night vision and other accessories. The built-in NVG shroud utilizes an integrated Wilcox machined aluminum shroud insert. Black colored version.

helmet.name: Team Wendy EXFIL Ballistic Helmet (Coyote Brown)
helmet.description: One of the most recent tactical ballistic helmets with extensive customization capabilities. The EXFIL LTP (Lightweight, Tactical, Polymer) bump helmet provides impact protection for maritime environments and a stable, comfortable platform for mounting night vision and other accessories. The built-in NVG shroud utilizes an integrated Wilcox machined aluminum shroud insert. Coyote Brown colored version.

helmet.name: MSA Gallet TC 800 High Cut combat helmet (Black)
helmet.description: The MSA TC 800 ballistic helmet, designed for use by tactical teams of police special forces, in combat and reconnaissance operations. It can be modified by various components.

helmet.name: Tac-Kek FAST MT helmet (Replica)
helmet.description: A lower protection class replica of the Ops-Core FAST MT Super High Cut Helmet from Tac-Kek. Features Ops-Core ARC Rails for attaching various components to the helmet.

helmet.name: Diamond Age Bastion helmet (Black)
helmet.description: According to the manufacturer - the Bastion helmet is the first combat helmet that can withstand a hit from a rifle, even with a bullet with an armored core at a muzzle speed.

helmet.name: Galvion Caiman Hybrid helmet (Grey)
helmet.description: The Caiman Hybrid helmet is a new generation of lightweight special forces helmet. A series of modular accessories enhances the package, providing users with lightweight, comfortable and maximum head protection. Manufactured by Galvion.

helmet.name: Rys-T bulletproof helmet (Black)
helmet.description: The "Rys-T" ("Lynx-T") armored helmet is an improved and lightweight version of the famous "Altyn" helmet. It is in service with the assault units of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russia. Can be equipped with a special armored visor.

helmet.name: Tagilla's welding mask "UBEY"
helmet.description: An armored steel welding mask of Tagilla - the Bossman of Factory. Painted with the special "UBEY" ("KILL") art.

helmet.name: Tagilla's welding mask "Gorilla"
helmet.description: An armored steel welding mask of Tagilla - the Bossman of Factory. Painted with the special "Gorilla" art.

helmet.name: NFM HJELM helmet (Hellhound Grey)
helmet.description: The new-gen HJELM system applies new ideas for modularity of attachments and electronics without the extra weight and bulk of previous generations. Manufactured by NFM.

headphones.name: Peltor ComTac II headset (OD Green)
headphones.description: The ComTac II amplifies low-level sounds while suppressing impulse noises. Water resistant for outdoor usage. Manufactured by Peltor.

headphones.name: Ops-Core FAST RAC Headset
headphones.description: A component for the Ops-Core FAST helmet - a system of noise reduction and amplification of quiet sounds, as well as a radio headset when connected to the communication device.

headphones.name: MSA Sordin Supreme PRO-X/L headset
headphones.description: The Sordin Supreme PRO-X/L headset amplifies low-level sounds while suppressing impulse noises. Water resistant for outdoor usage.

headphones.name: GSSh-01 active headset
headphones.description: The GSSh-01 headset is used in the Russian Ratnik military gear set.

headphones.name: Peltor Tactical Sport headset
headphones.description: The Peltor Tactical Sport electronic earmuff uses digital chip technology. It gives users fast shutoff and recovery time while helping protect ears from dangerous impulse noises, such as gunfire. Sound amplification allows the user to hear low-level sounds, including range commands and conversation.

headphones.name: Walker's Razor Digital headset
headphones.description: The Razor electronic ear muffs feature an ultra low-profile design and a rubberized coating for added durability and comfort, also providing optimal hearing protection. Manufactured by Walker's.

headphones.name: Walker's XCEL 500BT Digital headset
headphones.description: Active hearing protection with optimum electronic processing of ambient sounds without unnecessary distortion.

headphones.name: OPSMEN Earmor M32 headset
headphones.description: The EARMOR M32 headset is an activated electronic communication hearing protector, ideal for tactical use. Manufactured by OPSMEN.

headphones.name: Peltor ComTac IV Hybrid headset (Coyote Brown)
headphones.description: The ComTac IV Hybrid Communication Headset is designed to help reduce exposure to hazardous levels of noise, improve situational awareness and at the same time enable two-way radio communication in noisy environments. The headset's electronics are contained completely inside the headset housing, eliminating the need for a large, heavy external radio control box. The headband mechanically stabilizes the headset to help relieve issues of earplugs dislodging from cable snags and body movement. Designed for comfortable use with a ballistic helmet.

headphones.name: Safariland Liberator HP 2.0 Hearing Protection Headset (FDE)
headphones.description: A next generation low-profile active headset, designed to protect the user's hearing from external factors. Manufactured by Safariland. Flat Dark Earth version.

headphones.name: Peltor ComTac V headset (OD Green)
headphones.description: A communication headset equipped with a microphone and omnidirectional high-fidelity speakers that are optimized for voice communication and capable of picking up sounds with high sensitivity. Manufactured by 3M Peltor. OD Green color version.

headphones.name: Peltor ComTac VI headset (Coyote Brown)
headphones.description: An improved version of the ComTac V communication headset, equipped with advanced environmental listening settings and an NIB (Natural Interaction Behavior) feature, allowing to communicate with other ComTac VI users in a certain proximity without having to use radios. Manufactured by 3M Peltor. Coyote Brown version.

headphones.name: TW EXFIL Peltor ComTac V headset (OD Green)
headphones.description: A communication headset equipped with a microphone and omnidirectional high-fidelity speakers that are optimized for voice communication and capable of picking up sounds with high sensitivity. Equipped with a mount for attaching the headset to Team Wendy EXFIL helmets. Manufactured by 3M Peltor. OD Green color version.

headphones.name: TW EXFIL Peltor ComTac VI headset (Coyote Brown)

Untyped.name: Body armor repair kit
Untyped.description: A bag with everything you need to repair body armor - from the lightest to the heaviest.

Untyped.name: Weapon repair kit
Untyped.description: A set of tools and devices necessary to maintain firearms in operational condition.

Untyped.name: IMP mine detector
Untyped.description: A military mine detector. Can be useful when passing through a heavy mined space.

Untyped.name: Vortex Ranger 1500 rangefinder
Untyped.description: A handheld optical device that allows you to measure the distance to targets. Manufactured by Vortex Optics.

Untyped.name: Pumpkin with sweets
Untyped.description: Looks like someone in Tarkov decided to have some fun and scattered these pumpkins all over the place. There could definitely be something inside them.

Untyped.name: PR-Taran police baton
Untyped.description: The PR-Taran baton with side handle is used by law enforcement agencies for protection and crowd control.

Untyped.name: Diamond Age NeoSteel helmet ballistic mandible
Untyped.description: An extra ballistic protection with a special design for the Diamond Age NeoSteel helmet.

Untyped.name: Encrypted flash drive
Untyped.description: One of many thumb drives scattered around Tarkov. Contains the login kostochkin_g_b from ARRS Terminal.

Untyped.name: Akula push dagger
Untyped.description: As dangerous as the fish it's named after.

Untyped.name: Girl poster
Untyped.description: A simple poster of a girl. Perfect for a rest area.

Untyped.name: Girl poster
Untyped.description: A simple poster of a girl. A little weathered in some spots, but still pleasing to the eye.

Untyped.name: Girl poster
Untyped.description: A simple poster of a girl. So simple that every man in Tarkov had probably seen it at least once.

Untyped.name: Girl poster
Untyped.description: A simple poster of a girl. Not perfect condition, but it's doubtful you could find a better one.

Untyped.name: Girl poster
Untyped.description: A rare poster of a girl. It is said that someone pawned five gold teeth for one of these. Who they used to belong to is not stated.

Untyped.name: Special girl poster
Untyped.description: A poster that has truly become legendary. Only a few people have one of these.

Untyped.name: Bison vs Undertaker poster
Untyped.description: A poster from the Arena. It depicts the at the time legendary gladiators. So many Scavs came to see them fight that there weren't enough seats in the stands. Nowadays, nobody even remembers who won.

Untyped.name: Arena poster
Untyped.description: A blatant advertisement for making money in the Arena. Many Tarkov citizens were tempted by the quick money, despite risking death.

Untyped.name: Arena poster
Untyped.description: A poster advertising making money in the Arena. Sure, you can make money, but you can also die.

Untyped.name: Killa and Tagilla poster
Untyped.description: A poster with Killa and Tagila as anime girls. If only they were real.

Untyped.name: Alex Green poster
Untyped.description: A poster of the avant-garde composer Alex Green. His music is multifaceted and unique, so much so that the world's leading media wrote about him. People used to pay huge sums of money to visit his concerts.

Untyped.name: Things Sure Are Strange poster
Untyped.description: A rare poster of the movie which was never released. Director N. Tankovsky said in an interview that the story would be about a young security guard who began to notice mystical strange things going on in Tarkov.

Untyped.name: TerraGroup Labs advertisement
Untyped.description: At one point, the whole Tarkov was flooded with advertisements like this. But for some reason this particular poster is subtly different.

Untyped.name: Geneburn concert advertisement
Untyped.description: A rare poster. The concert was held overseas. Why were these posters put up all over Tarkov? No one knows to this day, but conspiracy theories are rampant.

Untyped.name: Exodus poster
Untyped.description: A regular poster of yet another movie from the director A. Bambetov.

Untyped.name: Den of Wolves poster
Untyped.description: A regular poster for the unreleased movie Den of Wolves. Nothing special, just a wolf.

Untyped.name: Highway poster
Untyped.description: An unknown artist tried to envision what a highway will look like in 2028. What is it: a flight of fancy or a subtle warning?

Untyped.name: Hell of Highwater poster
Untyped.description: A poster for the movie Hell of Highwater. The big screens never ran it, but Tarkov still has enough of these posters left to use as decoration.

Untyped.name: Gunfight poster
Untyped.description: A poster for the action thriller Gunfight from the studio Battle Star. Years ago, cinemas used to have massive waiting lines for movie. Now all that's left are the posters. It's a nice reminder of the old days.

Untyped.name: Last Flight poster
Untyped.description: The thriller Last Flight did not win any awards, but the box office collected a decent amount of cash. The director of the movie, Yulin Kontorsky, must have been overjoyed.

Untyped.name: Spooky Movie poster
Untyped.description: The studio Bubble Step did a pretty good job on their debut horror film Spooky Movie. Too bad they didn't have enough imagination for the title.

Untyped.name: Vasily poster
Untyped.description: The movie Vasily from the legendary director Nikita Bayanov. It held the box office lead for 28 weeks, owing in no small part to its deep and unusual plot.

Untyped.name: RUN poster
Untyped.description: The poster is not wordy, but straightforward. It'll look great at the front door. Or the exit door?

Untyped.name: Sharpshooter poster
Untyped.description: The movie Sharpshooter never came out. A real shame. The poster's kinda stylish.

Untyped.name: The Ambush poster
Untyped.description: A poster of the movie The Ambush. Although, in the end, the audience didn't see anything other than posters.

Untyped.name: The Hunted poster
Untyped.description: A poster for the unreleased movie The Hunted. Something about this style reminds of... A sequel to another unreleased project?

Untyped.name: USEC poster
Untyped.description: A poster of the unreleased movie USEC. It seems that this is how they wanted to fill the ranks of PMC operatives.
